# Telnyx Integration Patterns

## SDK & Libraries

- `@telnyx/ai-agent-lib` — AI assistant management
- `@telnyx/webrtc` — WebRTC for browser-based calls
- Telnyx REST API v2 for voice, messaging, numbers

## Configuration

- Telnyx config: `apps/tenant/src/core/telnyx/config.ts`
- Voice router: `apps/tenant/src/core/telnyx/voice-router.ts`
- Webhook transport: `apps/tenant/src/core/telnyx/webhook-transport.ts`

## Server Actions

Place Telnyx actions in `app/actions/telnyx/`:
- `assistants.ts` — AI assistant CRUD
- `messagingProfiles.ts` — messaging profile management
- `numbers.ts` — phone number management

## Webhook Handling

- Webhooks arrive at `app/api/webhooks/telnyx/`
- Always verify webhook signatures
- Use the call event handler at `app/api/webhooks/telnyx/call-events/route.ts`

## Skills Available

Telnyx Agent Skills are in `.cursor/skills/` (see `.cursor/rules/telnyx-agent-skills.mdc` for the full list and usage). Reference them for SDK examples:
- **telnyx-messaging-javascript**, **telnyx-messaging-profiles-javascript** — SMS/MMS, profiles, short codes
- **telnyx-voice-javascript**, **telnyx-voice-media-javascript** — Call control, playback, TTS, recording
- **telnyx-numbers-javascript** — Search, order, manage numbers
- **telnyx-verify-javascript** — OTP, lookup, 2FA
- **telnyx-ai-assistants-javascript** — AI voice assistants, knowledge bases
- **telnyx-sip-javascript** — SIP trunking, outbound voice profiles
